node.title: No danger to New Lynn community after person's death - police
node.description: Auckland police believe the death of a person in West Auckland yesterday was not a random incident.
node.content:
["Auckland police believe the death of a person in West Auckland yesterday was not a random incident.", "", "
Police responding to the incident in New Lynn yesterday. Photo: RNZ / Leith Huffadine
", "Officers were called to a house on Great North Road in New Lynn about 10am after being told that a gun had been fired.", "They found a person injured in the driveway and first aid was given, but the person died.", "Detective Inspector Kevin McNaughton said there is no suggestion that there is any danger to the wider community.", "He said while the police were grateful for the help they have received so far, they would like anyone else who has information to get in touch.", "Police can be contacted on 105 quoting the file number 211105/9752 or by calling Crime Stoppers anonymously on 0800 555 111."]
